reviewText: The Last of the Belles (1974) ...Susan Sarandon -- We enjoy movies from the 1930's to present day, so the issue date of 1974 was not the problem with the movie.  I found it slow and dark and boring.  Perhaps in 1974 I would have felt differently, but this shed no light on the writer of the Great Gatsby and portrayed F. Scott Fitzgerald (maybe accurately; don't know) as always dark and moody, alluding to all writers being so predisposed. That is not true. Very disappointed..
summary: The Last of the Belles (1974) ... Susan Sarandon
